### React Droppable Component Implementation with DndKit

Source: https://docs.dndkit.com/introduction/getting-started

This code defines a Droppable component using DndKit's useDroppable hook. It manages the visual feedback for when a draggable item is over the droppable area and provides a ref for DOM manipulation. It depends on '@dnd-kit/core'.

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import {useDroppable} from '@dnd-kit/core';

export function Droppable(props) {
  const {isOver, setNodeRef} = useDroppable({
    id: 'droppable',
  });
  const style = {
    color: isOver ? 'green' : undefined,
  };


  return (
    <div ref={setNodeRef} style={style}>
      {props.children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

