### Custom Snap to Grid Modifier Implementation

Source: https://docs.dndkit.com/api-documentation/modifiers

Provides a manual implementation example for a custom snap-to-grid modifier. This function calculates the new x and y coordinates by rounding the current transform values to the nearest grid multiple.

```javascript
const gridSize = 20;

function snapToGrid(args) {
  const {transform} = args;

  return {
    ...transform,
    x: Math.ceil(transform.x / gridSize) * gridSize,
    y: Math.ceil(transform.y / gridSize) * gridSize,
  };
 }
```

