### Compose Pointer and Rectangle Collision Detection Algorithms

Source: https://docs.dndkit.com/api-documentation/context-provider/collision-detection-algorithms

Combines the 'pointerWithin' and 'rectIntersection' algorithms. It first checks for collisions using pointer coordinates and falls back to rectangle intersection if no pointer collisions are found. This is useful for improving precision and handling different sensor inputs.

```javascript
import {pointerWithin, rectIntersection} from '@dnd-kit/core';

function customCollisionDetectionAlgorithm(args) {
  // First, let's see if there are any collisions with the pointer
  const pointerCollisions = pointerWithin(args);

  // Collision detection algorithms return an array of collisions
  if (pointerCollisions.length > 0) {
    return pointerCollisions;
  }

  // If there are no collisions with the pointer, return rectangle intersections
  return rectIntersection(args);
};
```

